gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 132, Cavaliers 120
gameRecap.excerpt: De'Aaron Fox returned from a 5-game absence (ankle) and led the Kings to a 132-120 victory, with 28 points and six assists on 11-20 shooting. Keegan Murray (25 points, 5-8 3PT, eight rebounds), Domantas Sabonis (23 points, 10 assists, nine rebounds) and Kevin Huerter (20 points, 6-9 3PT) totaled 68 points in the win for Sacramento. Donovan Mitchell led the Cavaliers with 22 points and five assists while Evan Mobley added 16 points and 11 rebounds. The Kings shot 20-42 from beyond the arc, reaching a new season-high in 3PT made while the 132 points tied a season-high.
